HEADWORD: Mineralogist
<hw>Min`er*al"o*gist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>min⟦eacute⟧ralogiste</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One versed in mineralogy; one devoted to the study
of minerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A carrier shell
(<spn>Phorus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mineralogize</ent>⟦br⟧
